ABUJA – Six hundred students cut across the country yesterday got a scholarship worth N120 million from the National Youth Council of Nigeria (NYCN) and Belema Oil Producing Limited. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network The scholarship was to commemorate the International Youth Day (IYD). Samuel Abl-Jumbo, the External Affairs Manager of Belema oil, who disclosed this at Aztect Alcrum Stadium road, Port Harcourt, Friday said the 2019 IYD theme “Transforming Education” is important, because education is fundamental to the development of youths and the nation. He said: “Belema oil is a household name in Nigeria and beyond. This scholarship is to support and say to the youth that we have confidence in our youth. We believe in them and we shall continue to support them.